%S A253810 0,14,21,33,38,80,84
%N A253810 The life of Diophantus.
%C A253810 From the riddle on the tombstone of Diophantus. See the reference and the links.
%D A253810 H.-W. Alten et al., 4000 Jahre Algebra, 2. Auflage, Springer, 2014, p. 63.
%H A253810 David Pleacher, <a href="http://www.pleacher.com/mp/mfacts/dioph.html">Diophantus' epitaph</a>.
%H A253810 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/DiophantussRiddle.html">Diophantus's Riddle</a>.
%H A253810 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diophantus">Diophantus</a>.
%F A253810 a(0): birth (all numbers a(n) in years), a(1): boyhood ended, a(2): beard started to grow, a(3): marriage, a(4): birth of son, a(5): death of son, a(6): death of Diophantus.
%e A253810 a(1) = age/6,
%e A253810 a(2) = age*(1/6 + 1/12) = age/4,
%e A253810 a(3) = age*(1/4 + 1/7) = age*11/28,
%e A253810 a(4) = age*11/28 + 5,
%e A253810 a(5) = age(11/28 + 1/2) + 5 = age*25/28 + 5,
%e A253810 a(6) = age*25/28 + 5 + 4 = age,
%e A253810 hence age*(1-25/28) = 9, age = 28*3 = 84.
%K A253810 nonn,fini,full
